<h2 headerid="4" name="text"><a id="StateTeacherLicensure" name="StateTeacherLicensure"></a>State Teacher Licensure</h2>
<p>BA in Urban Education, BA in the Teaching of English, BA in the Teaching of French, BA in the Teaching of German, BA in the Teaching of Spanish, BA in the Teaching of History, BS in the Teaching of Math, BS in the Teaching of Physics (suspended)</p>
<p>The curricula for the preparation of elementary and secondary school teachers as listed in this catalog have been approved by the Illinois Board of Higher Education, the Illinois State Board of Education, and the university.</p>
<h2 headerid="5" name="text"><strong><a id="StateAuthorization" name="StateAuthorization"></a>State Authorization for Online Programs and Courses</strong></h2>
<p>UIC must comply with state regulations concerning the delivery of online courses and programs to out-of-state students. UIC was approved by the Illinois Board of Higher Education to participate in the National Council for State Authorization Reciprocity Agreements (NC-SARA), which is intended to ease the workload of institutions seeking authorization to deliver online programs and courses in other states.</p>
<p>While students from most states may enroll in online programs at UIC, there are some important limitations.  Out-of-state students interested in enrolling in a UIC online program or online courses should check the <a href="https://ec.uic.edu/state-authorization/" target="_blank">State Authorization webpage</a> for more information about the states in which UIC is approved to offer distance education programs.</p>
<p>Students interested in online programs may contact UIC Extended Campus at <a href="mailto:onlineinfo@uic.edu">onlineinfo@uic.edu</a> or (312) 355-0423 for more program information.</p></div><!--end #textcontainer -->



